      <div class="msgContentFrame">Heavy thrust = Good in parties, Light thrust = Good soloing. The proc from heavy thrust while soloing is negligable, and is not worth the extra stamina cost. <br /> <br />To switch the two: <br /> <br />/equip main &quot;Brass Spear&quot; (Light thrust = Slot 1, Heavy Thrust unbound) <br />/eaction 10 &quot;Heavy Thrust&quot; (Light thrust = Slot 1, Heavy thrust = Slot 10) <br />/eaction 1 &quot;Heavy Thrust&quot; (Light Thrust = Slot 10, Heavy thrust = slot 1) <br /> <br />Skewer is trash. Only good in guildleves, which you will find give horrible SP the higher and higher you get in ranks. <br /> <br />After thinking about it, my bar is now:  <br />(Partying) <br />Ferocity / Raging Strike / Speed Surge / Invigorate <br />Heavy Thrust / Moonrise / Trammel / Comrade <br />Feint <br /> <br />Trammel &gt; Moonrise against low TP monsters such as Crabs. Also, Trammel is worthless if the debuff stays on, and that debuff lasts a pretty long time.</div>
